Another post-election fire outbreak has killed six members of the same family in the city of Kano, Kano State. Similar fire outbreak occurred in Kano after the 2015 elections which killed the Resident Electoral Commissioner, REC, and his entire family at his residence.
The fire outbreak was said to have began early Saturday morning razing their home at Bawo Road, Hausawa Quarters.
The deceased, Isaiah Jonathan, his wife, three children, including a baby and his sister-in-law were burnt beyond recognition.
Kano Police Spokesman, Abdullahi Haruna, who confirmed the incident, said the fire was put off by men of the Kano Fire Service.

			
